  "response": "Becoming truly broad-minded about religion is a complex and gradual process that depends on several factors:\n\n1. Education\n- Promoting secular and inclusive education\n- Teaching respect for different religions\n- Encouraging critical thinking\n\n2. Social reforms\n- Reducing religious stereotypes\n- Promoting interfaith dialogue\n- Supporting progressive social movements\n\n3. Urban development\n- Increased exposure to diverse perspectives\n- More cosmopolitan and inclusive environments\n- Greater interaction between different communities\n\n4. Generational change\n- Younger generations tend to be more open-minded\n- Increased global connectivity\n- Access to diverse information through internet\n\n5. Political leadership\n- Promoting secular values\n- Discouraging religious polarization\n- Supporting inclusive policies\n\n6. Economic development\n- Better economic opportunities\n- Reduced dependence on religious identities\n- More focus on individual growth\n\n7. Media representation\n- Balanced and unbiased religious reporting\n- Promoting positive interfaith narratives\n- Challenging religious extremism\n\nProgress is gradual and depends on collective efforts from individuals, communities, institutions, and leadership. While challenges exist, continuous dialogue, education, and mutual understanding can help create a more inclusive society.",
